3/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-11-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-11-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-11-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-11-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-11-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>While the e3.1 comes with a mechanical SRAM SX Eagle 1×12 drivetrain, it’s nice to see that the frame includes a SRAM UDH making it Transmission-compatible in the future. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Build Specs</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-10.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-10-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"REI Co-Op Cycles e3.1 eMTB brake lever\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-10-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-10-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-10-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-10-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-10-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-10-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-10-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-14.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-14-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"REI Co-Op Cycles e3.1 eMTB stem\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-14-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-14-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-14-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-14-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-14-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-14-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-14-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-20.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-20-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"REI Co-Op Cycles e3.1 eMTB front hub\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-20-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-20-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-20-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-20-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-20-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-20-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-20-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-18.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-18-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"REI Co-Op Cycles e3.1 eMTB rear brake\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-18-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-18-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-18-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-18-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-18-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-18-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-18-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The rest of the build is high quality with an eye towards affordability with Tektro Gemini SL 4-piston hydraulic disc brakes, an X-Fusion Manic dropper post, a Co-Op branded aluminum bar and stem, and Co-Op branded tubeless-ready double-wall aluminum rims with Formula hubs. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-31.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-31-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Nevegal 2 pro tires\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-31-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-31-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-31-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-31-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-31-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-31-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-31-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The wheel size of the bike will depend on what size you ride. Extra Small and Small bikes will roll on 27.5 x 2.6″ tires, while Medium – Extra Large will get the full size 29 x 2.6″ tires. Stock bikes include tubeless-ready Kenda Nevegal 2 Pro tires and the rims come pre-taped, though you’ll have to add your own valve stems and tubeless sealant to ditch the tubes. Note that you’ll need a longer tubeless valve stem in the rear to accommodate the sensor on the rear wheel. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Geometry</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-Co-op-Cycles-DRT-e3.1-ebike-geometry.png\"><img width=\"2467\" height=\"1073\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-Co-op-Cycles-DRT-e3.1-ebike-geometry.png\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-Co-op-Cycles-DRT-e3.1-ebike-geometry.png 2467w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-Co-op-Cycles-DRT-e3.1-ebike-geometry-297x129.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-Co-op-Cycles-DRT-e3.1-ebike-geometry-800x348.png 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-Co-op-Cycles-DRT-e3.1-ebike-geometry-120x52.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-Co-op-Cycles-DRT-e3.1-ebike-geometry-768x334.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-Co-op-Cycles-DRT-e3.1-ebike-geometry-1536x668.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-Co-op-Cycles-DRT-e3.1-ebike-geometry-2048x891.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The geometry of the e3.1 is right on the money for modern mountain bikes without getting <em>too</em> crazy. A 66º head tube angle combined with a 77.4º seat tube angle (size M) and a 450mm reach should mean most novice to advanced riders will find themselves comfortable. REI lists the maximum weight limit for rider and cargo at 300lbs. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>For the bike itself, the claimed weight is 55lbs and our medium sample checked in at 54.7lbs. Go tubeless to drop it to 54.23lbs. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Included with Purchase</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-34.jpg\"><img width=\"2500\" height=\"1667\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-34.jpg\" alt=\"REI Co-Op Cycles e3.1 eMTB angle\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-34.jpg 2500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-34-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-34-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-34-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-34-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-34-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-34-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/REI-e3.1-Co-Op-eMTB-electric-mountain-bike-review-34-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Everyone who buys the Co-Op DRT e3.1 will receive Coast to Coast support which includes a year of free adjustments, and in-store bike assembly with the option to pick it up in-store or curbside. If you’re an REI Co-Op member, you get an additional year of free adjustments for two years total, free flat tire repairs (labor only), and an additional 20% off shop services. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new ebikes are available now for REI Co-Op member early access, with full availability in November. The e3.1 is only <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=10248&amp;pw=293233&amp;ctc=brprgearbikesgeneral&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F198759%2Fco-op-cycles-drt-e31-electric-mountain-bike\" target=\"_blank\">available in Bamboo color, for $4,999</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/reis-first-emtb-meet-the-co-op-cycles-drt-e3-1-w-bosch-smart-system/\">REI’s First eMTB: Meet the Co-Op Cycles DRT e3.1 w/ Bosch Smart System</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"fe8961accc5531e22ce93e87da84eb3059f0b9f4b1094c910adda9c1721273a6","category":"Cycling"}